body:
After upgrading the "Flutter" plugin to `63.0.5` in IntelliJ IDEA `2021.3`, my Flutter demo can run successfully. 
However, it showed me **"JxBrowser installation failed"** in "Flutter Inspector" panel, and no response when clicking the "Retry installation?" text button, related info in `idea.log` is: 

```

2021-12-02 21:45:49,618 [1096649]   INFO - ter.jxbrowser.JxBrowserManager - Loaded JxBrowser file successfully: ~/Library/Application Support/JetBrains/Toolbox/apps/IDEA-U/ch-0/213.5744.223/IntelliJ IDEA.app.plugins/flutter-intellij/jxbrowser/jxbrowser-7.19.jar

2021-12-02 21:45:49,618 [1096649]   INFO - ter.jxbrowser.JxBrowserManager - Failed to find JxBrowser class 
```

By the way, I don't know why there are **two** item for "Android Studio" and "IntelliJ IDEA" respectively in the output of `flutter doctor -v` for a while.

comment_data.body:
By checking the above crash backtrace and [flutter code](https://github.com/flutter/flutter/blob/2.5.3/packages/flutter_tools/lib/src/intellij/intellij_validator.dart#L103), it seems that the crash was triggered when invalidating `Dart` plugin.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/665595/144656245-fbfbbef8-483e-4636-bcb3-d1c74a45b5d3.png)

Flutter plugin 63.0.5 on 2021.3 does not work on M1 as well. Idea.log shows:
.
2021-12-05 12:51:29,700 [ 234232]   INFO - ter.jxbrowser.JxBrowserManager - Failed to find JxBrowser class
The issue has been fixed after upgrading to Flutter plugin 63.1.4 in my dev env.
I can confirm: issue fixed on M1 as well. And no workaround for loading the wrong chromium binary needed any longer.
